# Aether Core — environment configuration
#
# Every variable is optional. With none set, Aether runs against the built-in
# Fake provider (deterministic, offline). Real providers appear in the picker
# only when their credential is present (Ollama: when the daemon is reachable).
# Keys can also be set at runtime via the in-app Provider Auth pane (KeyVault),
# which is used whenever the matching env var below is absent.
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in what you need.

# --- Provider credentials ---

# Enable the Gemini provider.
# GEMINI_API_KEY=""

# Enable the Anthropic / Claude provider.
# (Claude CLI OAuth is auto-detected too, so this is optional if you're logged in.)
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=""

# Anthropic OAuth / Teams without an API key: generate a long-lived token with
# `claude setup-token` and set it here. Aether passes it explicitly to the
# spawned `claude`, so dispatch authenticates even though the agent runs in
# isolation mode (no interactive-login config is inherited).
# CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=""

# Enable the OpenAI provider.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=""

# Ollama daemon URL (local models are auto-discovered from /api/tags).
# OLLAMA_HOST="http://localhost:11434"

# --- Server / runtime ---

# HTTP port for the server (default: 3000).
# PORT="3000"

# Directory for the SQLite database (default: ./data).
# AETHER_DATA_DIR="./data"

# Force the default provider, e.g. "gemini:gemini-1.5-pro" or "anthropic:claude-opus-4-7".
# AETHER_DEFAULT_PROVIDER=""

# Set to 1 to force the deterministic Fake provider (useful for tests / offline dev).
# AETHER_FAKE_PROVIDER="0"

# Set to "production" to serve the prebuilt SPA from dist/ instead of the Vite dev server.
# NODE_ENV=""
